javadoc: Command to create an array inside of a structure.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for creating arrays inside of structures.

params.name: addr
params.comment: The address of the structure that will contain the new array.

params.name: numElements
params.comment: the number of elements in the array to be created.

params.name: dt
params.comment: the dataType of the elements in the array to be created.

params.name: compPath
params.comment:
the component path within the structure at which to create
 the array. The component path is an array of integers where each integer
 is a component index of the component above it.

name: CreateArrayInStructureCmd
comment: Command to create an array inside of a structure.
